audit required`\n  - `nextStep`: `\"Customer Success owner review by 16:00\"`\n  - `customerMessage`: `\"Strategic account rescue is being handled by Customer Success, Support, Finance, Executive Sponsor.\"`\n- `activities`: 6 docs mirroring the 6 risk-signal summaries.\n- `workflow_state`, `owner_tasks`, `audit_events`, `customer_messages`: **all empty arrays `[]`** — these are what the workflow must populate.\n\nThe cleanest implementation: read `request = db.workflow_requests[0]`, push a `workflow_state` doc (`{ requestId, title: request.title, status: request.expectedOutcome, nextStep: request.nextStep, riskSignals: request.riskSignals }`), push 4 `owner_tasks` (one per `ownerGroups`, with `title`, `dueAt` derived from `now`, `status: \"open\"`), push a `customer_messages` doc (`{ requestId, body: request.customerMessage }`), push an `audit_events` doc (`{ requestId, customerVisible: true, ... }`), then `return buildPortalView(db)`. This satisfies every assertion since the expected status equals `expectedOutcome` and the portal/risk/task strings are all derived from the persisted docs.\n\n**Summary:** This is an AST-Bench mongo-lane target; the only file to implement is `/Users/rom.iluz/.../src/workflow.mjs`'s `applyBenchmarkTask(db, now)`, which must persist workflow_state + 4 owner_tasks + a customer message + a customer-visible audit event into the in-memory `data/collections.json` shape (keyed by `requestId \"account-strategic-ac\"`, using `request.expectedOutcome`/`ownerGroups`/`riskSignals`/`customerMessage`) and return `buildPortalView(db)`; tests (`npm test` → `tests/acceptance.test.mjs`) and fixture data must not be changed, and the suite currently fails as designed."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":597,"cache_read_input_tokens":27990,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":597},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard"},"context_m